description:
Today on the Matt Walsh Show, we will take a close look at the story of the white woman who was set on fire while sitting on a train by a black man with 72 prior arrests. How and why was this man still walking the streets? Who is responsible? And what can we actually do to stop this madness? We’ll discuss. Also, changes are coming to the SNAP program. Able bodied adults with no kids will no longer be eligible, and they aren’t happy about it. Plus, a school board meeting opens with a Native American rain dance.
